NOT FOR ENGINEERING PURPOSES</useconst>     <datacred>United States Geological Survey (USGS) with post processing by Denver Environmental Health - Environmental Quality.</datacred>     <secinfo>       <secsys>AVAILABLE</secsys>       <secclass>Unclassified</secclass>       <sechandl>Available to the public and accessible through Denver\ufffd\ufffd\ufffds Open Data Catalog, http://data.denvergov.org/</sechandl>     </secinfo>     <native>Microsoft Windows Server 2008 R2 Version 6.1 (Build 7601) Service Pack 1; ESRI ArcGIS 10.0.5.4400</native>     <crossref>       <citeinfo>         <origin>Robson</origin>         <pubdate>19960101</pubdate>         <title>Geohydrology of the Shallow Water Aquifers in the Denver Metropolitan Area, Colorado</title>       </citeinfo>     </crossref>     <crossref>       <citeinfo>         <origin>Miller, L.Lee</origin>         <origin>Char, Stephen J.</origin>         <origin>Sieverling, Jennifer B.</origin>         <pubdate>19960101</pubdate>         <title>Bedrock Surface Altitude</title>       </citeinfo>     </crossref>   </idinfo>   <dataqual>     <complete>This shapefile was created by modifying a bedrock contour map for Denver which was downloaded from the USGS website.  See cross-references section for a full description of the sources.  The isolines of the USGS contour map were interpolated using the Topogrid function of ArcInfo.  The contour lines were used as the interpolation value.  A gridsize of 105 feet was used.  The commands used were as follows.   topogrid bdrk-g 125 contour bdrk-clip CONTOUR  datatype contour end  The grid was contoured at one-foot intervals to create a more detailed contour of the bedrock elevation beneath Denver. The following command was used to contour.  BEDROCK-1 = CONTOUR(BDRK-G, INTERVAL, 1, #)  </complete>   </dataqual>   <spdoinfo>     <direct>Vector</direct>     <ptvctinf>       <sdtsterm>         <sdtstype>String</sdtstype>         <ptvctcnt>16983</ptvctcnt>       </sdtsterm>     </ptvctinf>   </spdoinfo>   <spref>     <horizsys>       <geograph>         <latres>8.9831528411952133e-009</latres>         <longres>8.9831528411952133e-009</longres>         <geogunit>Decimal Degrees</geogunit>       </geograph>       <geodetic>         <horizdn>D WGS 1984</horizdn>         <ellips>WGS 1984</ellips>         <semiaxis>6378137.0</semiaxis>         <denflat>298.257223563</denflat>       </geodetic>     </horizsys>   </spref>   <eainfo>     <detailed>       <enttyp>         <enttypl>ENV_BEDROCKCONTOUR1FT_L</enttypl>       </enttyp>       <attr>         <attrlabl>OBJECTID</attrlabl>         <attrdef>Internal feature number.</attrdef>         <attrdefs>ESRI</attrdefs>         <attrdomv>           <udom>Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.</udom>         </attrdomv>       </attr>       <attr>         <attrlabl>CONTOUR</attrlabl>         <attrdef>Elevation for specified line.
